{"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "C:\\QAx\\002\\context-pack\\development-guidelines.md", "content": "1: # Development Guidelines\n2: # Star Wars Lego — Greenfield\n3: \n4: **Document Version:** 1.0\n5: \n6: ## 1. Coding Standards\n7: \n8: ### JavaScript ES6+ Conventions\n9: - **Naming:** camelCase for variables and functions\n10: - **Constants:** UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants\n11: - **Functions:** Clear, descriptive function names\n12: - **Comments:** Educational comments for learning purposes\n13: - **File Organization:** Logical grouping of related functionality\n14: \n15: ### Vue.js Best Practices\n16: - **Component Names:** kebab-case for component registration\n17: - **Props:** Explicit prop declaration with types\n18: - **Data:** Return functions for component data\n19: - **Methods:** Verb-based method names\n20: - **Templates:** Clean, readable HTML structure\n21: \n22: ### CSS Guidelines\n23: - **Class Names:** kebab-case for CSS classes\n24: - **Organization:** Logical grouping of styles\n25: - **Responsiveness:** Mobile-first approach (from 820px)\n26: - **Performance:** Efficient selectors and properties\n27: \n28: ## 2. File Organization Standards\n29: \n30: ### Proposed Directory Structure\n31: ```\n32: star-wars-lego/\n33: ├── index.html                    # Main application entry\n34: ├── css/\n35: │   ├── reset.css                 # CSS reset (assumption)\n36: │   ├── variables.css             # CSS custom properties\n37: │   ├── layout.css                # Grid and layout styles\n38: │   ├── components.css            # Component-specific styles\n39: │   └── main.css                  # Main stylesheet entry point\n40: ├── js/\n41: │   ├── app.js                    # Vue.js application root\n42: │   ├── router.js                 # Route handling (if needed)\n43: │   ├── components/\n44: │   │   ├── CharacterGallery.js   # Character gallery component\n45: │   │   ├── SearchBox.js          # Search functionality\n46: │   │   ├── CharacterCard.js      # Individual character display\n47: │   │   └── Notification.js       # Alert system\n48: │   ├── data/\n49: │   │   └── characters.js         # Character data source\n50: │   └── utils/\n51: │       ├── helpers.js            # Utility functions\n52: │       └── constants.js          # Application constants\n53: ├── assets/\n54: │   ├── images/                   # Character and UI images\n55: │   │   ├── characters/          # Character images\n56: │   │   └── ui/                   # UI elements\n57: │   └── icons/                    # Icon resources\n58: └── libs/                         # External libraries\n59:     ├── vue.js                    # Vue.js framework\n60:     └── (other libraries as needed)\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ## 3. Component Development Standards\n64: \n65: ### Vue.js Component Structure Template\n66: ```javascript\n67: // Component Template\n68: Vue.component('component-name', {\n69:   // Component props with type validation\n70:   props: {\n71:     propName: {\n72:       type: String,\n73:       required: true,\n74:       default: 'default-value'\n75:     }\n76:   },\n77: \n78:   // Component data (must be a function)\n79:   data() {\n80:     return {\n81:       internalState: 'initial-value'\n82:     };\n83:   },\n84: \n85:   // Computed properties for derived data\n86:   computed: {\n87:     computedProperty() {\n88:       return this.transformData(this.propName);\n89:     }\n90:   },\n91: \n92:   // Component methods for user interactions\n93:   methods: {\n94:     handleUserAction() {\n95:       // Action handling logic\n96:       this.updateInternalState();\n97:     },\n98: \n99:     updateInternalState() {\n100:       this.internalState = 'new-value';\n101:       this.$emit('state-changed', this.internalState);\n102:     }\n103:   },\n104: \n105:   // Component template\n106:   template: `\n107:     <div class=\"component-name\">\n108:       <h2>{{ computedProperty }}</h2>\n109:       <button @click=\"handleUserAction\">\n110:         Action Button\n111:       </button>\n112:     </div>\n113:   `\n114: });\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ### Component Naming Conventions\n118: - **File Names:** PascalCase (e.g., CharacterGallery.js)\n119: - **Component Names:** kebab-case in HTML (character-gallery)\n120: - **Class Names:** kebab-case CSS classes (character-gallery)\n121: \n122: ## 4. Styling Guidelines\n123: \n124: ### CSS Architecture\n125: - ** methodologies:** Component-based CSS organization\n126: - **Custom Properties:** CSS variables for theming\n127: - **Responsive Design:** Mobile-first from 820px breakpoint\n128: - **Performance:** Efficient selectors and minimal specificity\n129: \n130: ### CSS Class Naming Convention\n131: ```css\n132: /* Block-level component */\n133: .component-name {\n134:   /* Component styles */\n135: }\n136: \n137: /* Element within component */\n138: .component-name__element {\n139:   /* Element-specific styles */\n140: }\n141: \n142: /* Modifier for component state */\n143: .component-name--modifier {\n144:   /* State-specific styles */\n145: }\n146: ```\n147: \n148: ### Color System Variables\n149: ```css\n150: :root {\n151:   /* Star Wars Theme Colors */\n152:   --color-bg-primary: #111;           /* Background */\n153:   --color-text-primary: #CCC;         /* Main text */\n154:   --color-accent-primary: #FD4;       /* Star Wars yellow */\n155:   --color-alert: #FF4444;            /* Alert red */\n156: \n157:   /* Typography */\n158:   --font-primary: 'Acme', sans-serif;\n159:   --font-secondary: 'Handlee', cursive;\n160: \n161:   /* Layout */\n162:   --container-min-width: 820px;\n163:   --spacing-unit: 1rem;\n164: }\n165: ```\n166: \n167: ## 5. Data Management Standards\n168: \n169: ### Character Data Structure\n170: ```javascript\n171: // Data structure for character information\n172: const CHARACTER_SCHEMA = {\n173:   id: 'number',                    // Unique identifier\n174:   name: 'string',                  // Character name\n175:   image: 'string',                 // Image file path\n176:   description: 'string',           // Character description\n177:   liked: 'boolean',                // Like status\n178:   deleted: 'boolean',              // Deletion status\n179:   category: 'string'               // Character category (assumption)\n180: };\n181: ```\n182: \n183: ### Data Access Patterns\n184: ```javascript\n185: // Vue.js data property interaction\n186: const app = new Vue({\n187:   el: '#app',\n188:   data: {\n189:     characters: [],                 // Character collection\n190:     searchQuery: '',               // Search input\n191:     selectedCharacter: null,       // Currently selected character\n192:     userGreeting: 'Welcome!'       // Personalized greeting\n193:   },\n194: \n195:   methods: {\n196:     // Search functionality\n197:     searchCharacters() {\n198:       return this.characters.filter(character =>\n199:         character.name.toLowerCase()\n200:           .includes(this.searchQuery.toLowerCase())\n201:       );\n202:     },\n203: \n204:     // Like functionality\n205:     toggleLike(characterId) {\n206:       const character = this.characters.find(c => c.id === characterId);\n207:       if (character) {\n208:         character.liked = !character.liked;\n209:         this.showNotification(`${character.name} ${character.liked ? 'liked' : 'unliked'}!`);\n210:       }\n211:     },\n212: \n213:     // Delete functionality\n214:     deleteCharacter(characterId) {\n215:       const index = this.characters.findIndex(c => c.id === characterId);\n216:       if (index !== -1) {\n217:         const character = this.characters[index];\n218:         this.characters.splice(index, 1);\n219:         this.showNotification(`${character.name} removed from gallery!`);\n220:       }\n221:     },\n222: \n223:     // Notification system\n224:     showNotification(message) {\n225:       // Alert display logic (assumed implementation)\n226:       console.log(message); // Placeholder for actual notification system\n227:     }\n228:   },\n229: \n230:   computed: {\n231:     // Computed search results\n232:     filteredCharacters() {\n233:       return this.searchQuery ? this.searchCharacters() : this.characters;\n234:     },\n235: \n236:     // Character statistics\n237:     characterStats() {\n238:       return {\n239:         total: this.characters.length,\n240:         liked: this.characters.filter(c => c.liked).length,\n241:         deleted: this.characters.filter(c => c.deleted).length\n242:       };\n243:     }\n244:   }\n245: });\n246: ```\n247: \n248: ## 6. Educational Documentation Standards\n249: \n250: ### Code Comments Requirements\n251: ```javascript\n252: /**\n253:  * Filters characters based on search query\n254:  * @param {Array} characters - Array of character objects\n255:  * @param {string} query - Search query string\n256:  * @returns {Array} Filtered array of characters\n257:  * @example\n258:  * const results = filterCharacters(characters, 'Luke');\n259:  * console.log(results); // [{ name: 'Luke Skywalker', ... }]\n260:  */\n261: function filterCharacters(characters, query) {\n262:   // toLowerCase() makes search case-insensitive\n263:   // includes() checks if the query exists in character names\n264:   return characters.filter(character =>\n265:     character.name.toLowerCase().includes(query.toLowerCase())\n266:   );\n267: }\n268: ```\n269: \n270: ### README Documentation Structure\n271: ```markdown\n272: # Star Wars Lego - Interactive JavaScript Learning\n273: \n274: ## Learning Objectives\n275: - Practice ES6+ JavaScript features\n276: - Implement Vue.js reactive patterns\n277: - Build interactive user interfaces\n278: \n279: ## Key Concepts Demonstrated\n280: - Array filtering and manipulation\n281: - Event handling and DOM interaction\n282: - Component-based architecture\n283: - Reactive data binding\n284: \n285: ## Development Setup\n286: 1. Clone the repository\n287: 2. Open index.html in a modern browser\n288: 3. Start experimenting with the code!\n289: ```\n290: \n291: ## 7. Performance Optimization Guidelines\n292: \n293: ### Image Optimization\n294: - **Format:** WebP or optimized JPEG\n295: - **Sizing:** Appropriate dimensions for display size\n296: - **Loading:** Lazy loading for character images\n297: \n298: ### JavaScript Efficiency\n299: - **DOM Updates:** Batch DOM modifications\n300: - **Event Listeners:** Proper event delegation\n301: - **Memory Management:** Clean up event listeners and intervals\n302: \n303: ### CSS Performance\n304: - **Animations:** Use transform and opacity for smooth animations\n305: - **Selectors:** Efficient CSS selectors\n306: - **Critical Path:** Optimize CSS delivery for fast rendering\n307: \n308: ## 8. Testing Guidelines\n309: \n310: ### Manual Testing Checklist\n311: - [ ] All interactive elements respond correctly\n312: - [ ] Search functionality works with various inputs\n313: - [ ] Like/unlike functionality updates UI properly\n314: - [ ] Delete functionality removes items correctly\n315: - [ ] Visual feedback displays appropriately\n316: - [ ] Responsive layout works at different screen sizes\n317: - [ ] Cross-browser compatibility verified\n318: \n319: ### Educational Validation\n320: - [ ] Code demonstrates intended JavaScript concepts\n321: - [ ] Examples are clear and easy to understand\n322: - [ ] Comments provide adequate learning context\n323: - [ ] Functionality matches educational objectives\n324: \n325: ---\n326: \n327: *Star Wars Lego Development Guidelines — Globant Delivery Team*", "metadata": {"start_line": 1, "end_line": 327, "returned_lines": 327, "has_more": false, "eof_reached": true, "truncated": false}}}
