{"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "C:\\QAx\\002\\context-pack\\technical-requirements.md", "content": "1: # Technical Requirements\n2: # Star Wars Lego — Greenfield\n3: \n4: **Document Version:** 1.0\n5: \n6: ## 1. Development Environment Setup\n7: \n8: ### Required Tools\n9: - **Code Editor:** Modern JavaScript-capable IDE\n10: - **Browser:** Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge (latest versions)\n11: - **Local Server:** Optional, for development convenience\n12: - **Version Control:** Git for source management\n13: \n14: ### File Structure (Assumption)\n15: ```\n16: star-wars-lego/\n17: ├── index.html              # Main application entry point\n18: ├── css/\n19: │   ├── main.css            # Main stylesheet\n20: │   └── components.css      # Component-specific styles\n21: ├── js/\n22: │   ├── app.js              # Vue.js application entry\n23: │   ├── components/         # Vue components\n24: │   └── utils/              # Utility functions\n25: ├── assets/\n26: │   └── images/             # Character images\n27: └── libs/                   # External libraries (Vue.js)\n28: ```\n29: \n30: ## 2. Frontend Technology Specifications\n31: \n32: ### HTML5 Requirements\n33: - **Semantic Markup:** Use appropriate HTML5 semantic elements\n34: - **Validation:** HTML5 compliant structure\n35: - **Accessibility:** Basic ARIA attributes for screen readers\n36: - **SEO:** Meta tags for basic search optimization\n37: \n38: ### CSS3 Specifications\n39: - **Layout System:** CSS Grid for main layout structure\n40: - **Responsive Design:** Media queries for viewport adaptation\n41: - **Animation:** CSS transitions for hover effects and interactions\n42: - **Typography:** Google Fonts integration (Acme, Handlee)\n43: \n44: ### JavaScript ES6+ Features\n45: - **Functions:** Arrow functions, function expressions\n46: - **Objects:** Object literals, property access\n47: - **Arrays:** Array methods (forEach, map, filter, find)\n48: - **Loops:** Traditional and modern iteration patterns\n49: - **DOM Manipulation:** Event handling, element modification\n50: \n51: ## 3. Vue.js 2.x Implementation\n52: \n53: ### Core Vue.js Features\n54: - **Data Binding:** Two-way data binding for form inputs\n55: - **Directives:** v-if, v-for, v-model, v-bind, v-on\n56: - **Computed Properties:** Dynamic calculations and filtering\n57: - **Component Architecture:** Reusable Vue components\n58: - **Event Handling:** Custom events and event propagation\n59: \n60: ### Vue.js Component Structure (Assumption)\n61: ```javascript\n62: // Character Gallery Component\n63: Vue.component('character-gallery', {\n64:   props: ['characters'],\n65:   template: `\n66:     <div class=\"character-gallery\">\n67:       <div v-for=\"character in characters\" \n68:            :key=\"character.id\" \n69:            class=\"character-card\"\n70:            @click=\"selectCharacter(character)\">\n71:         <!-- Character display content -->\n72:       </div>\n73:     </div>\n74:   `\n75: });\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### State Management\n79: - **Local State:** Component-level data properties\n80: - **Props/Events:** Parent-child communication\n81: - **No Vuex:** Simplified state management assumed\n82: \n83: ## 4. Data Structures and Models\n84: \n85: ### Character Data Model (Assumption)\n86: ```javascript\n87: const character = {\n88:   id: Number,           // Unique identifier\n89:   name: String,         // Character name\n90:   image: String,        // Image file path\n91:   description: String,  // Character description\n92:   liked: Boolean,       // Like status\n93:   deleted: Boolean      // Deletion status\n94: };\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ### Application State Structure\n98: ```javascript\n99: const appData = {\n100:   characters: Array,     // Character collection\n101:   searchQuery: String,   // Search input value\n102:   greeting: String,      // Personalized message\n103:   totalCount: Number     // Active character count\n104: };\n105: ```\n106: \n107: ## 5. User Interaction Specifications\n108: \n109: ### Search Functionality\n110: - **Real-time Filtering:** Live search as user types\n111: - **Required Field:** Search input validation\n112: - **Filter Logic:** Case-insensitive name matching\n113: - **Reset Capability:** Clear search functionality\n114: \n115: ### Character Interactions\n116: - **Like/Favorite:** Toggle like status with visual feedback\n117: - **Delete:** Remove character with confirmation (assumption)\n118: - **Hover Effects:** CSS transitions and visual enhancements\n119: - **Selection:** Character selection for detailed view (assumption)\n120: \n121: ### User Feedback Systems\n122: - **Visual Alerts:** Non-blocking notification system\n123: - **Status Updates:** Real-time feedback for user actions\n124: - **Loading States:** Visual indicators for async operations (if needed)\n125: \n126: ## 6. Performance Requirements\n127: \n128: ### Loading Performance (Assumption)\n129: - **Initial Load:** < 3 seconds for complete application\n130: - **Image Loading:** Optimized formats and lazy loading\n131: - **Font Loading:** Async font loading strategies\n132: - **JavaScript:** Minified and compressed delivery\n133: \n134: ### Runtime Performance\n135: - **Search Performance:** Efficient filtering algorithms\n136: - **Animation Performance:** 60fps CSS transitions\n137: - **Memory Usage:** Efficient DOM manipulation\n138: - **Event Handling:** Proper event delegation\n139: \n140: ## 7. Browser Compatibility Matrix\n141: \n142: | Browser | Minimum Version | Support Level |\n143: |---------|----------------|---------------|\n144: | Chrome | 90+ | Full |\n145: | Firefox | 88+ | Full |\n146: | Safari | 14+ | Full |\n147: | Edge | 90+ | Full |\n148: \n149: ### Feature Support Requirements\n150: - **ES6+:** Full support for modern JavaScript features\n151: - **CSS Grid:** Layout system support\n152: - **Flexbox:** Additional layout capabilities\n153: - **Web APIs:** Local storage, fetch (if needed)\n154: \n155: ## 8. Security Considerations\n156: \n157: ### Client-Side Security\n158: - **Input Validation:** Sanitize user inputs\n159: - **XSS Prevention:** Proper content encoding\n160: - **Data Privacy:** No personal data storage (assumption)\n161: - **Resource Loading:** Secure asset loading practices\n162: \n163: ## 9. Testing Requirements (Assumption)\n164: \n165: ### Manual Testing Focus\n166: - **Functionality:** All interactive features working\n167: - **Visual Design:** Consistent appearance across browsers\n168: - **Responsiveness:** Layout adaptation at different viewports\n169: - **Performance:** Acceptable loading and interaction times\n170: \n171: ### Cross-Browser Testing\n172: - **Primary Targets:** Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge\n173: - **Viewport Testing:** Desktop and tablet sizes (820px+)\n174: - **Interaction Testing:** All user interactive elements\n175: \n176: ## 10. Deployment Specifications\n177: \n178: ### Production Environment\n179: - **Static Hosting:** File-based web server\n180: - **No Server-Side:** Pure client-side application\n181: - **CDN Usage:** Optional for Vue.js and Google Fonts\n182: - **Asset Optimization:** Compressed images and minified code\n183: \n184: ### File Delivery\n185: - **HTML:** Single index.html file\n186: - **CSS:** Combined and minified stylesheets\n187: - **JavaScript:** Bundled Vue.js and application code\n188: - **Images:** Optimized web formats\n189: \n190: ---\n191: \n192: *Star Wars Lego Technical Requirements — Globant Delivery Team*", "metadata": {"start_line": 1, "end_line": 192, "returned_lines": 192, "has_more": false, "eof_reached": true, "truncated": false}}}
